radiographic_examinations.findings: A tiny nodular opacity in the right lung base likely represents vessel seen en face, mild atelectasis in the cardiophrenic angles, lungs clear without pleural effusion, heart normal in size without pericardial effusion, two subcentimeter poorly marginated hypodense lesions in the liver, gallbladder with no definite evidence of stone, normal spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands, bilateral kidneys enhancing symmetrically, a 3-mm rounded hyperdensity adjacent to the right ureterovesicular junction suggestive of phlebolith, the stomach collapsed with hyperdense ingested material, small and large bowel loops normal, appendix measuring up to 9-mm without definite adjacent fat stranding, and no free air or fluid.
